
[1]scarp

   SC'ARP, n.

   In fortification, the interior talus or slope of the ditch next the
   place, at the foot of the rampart.

    SC'ARP, n. In heraldry, the scarf which military commanders wear for
     ornament; borne somewhat like a battoon sinister, but broader, and
                    continued to the edges of the field.
